Across the resource-rich countries, companies are suspending operations.
Foreign companies such as the Arcelor Mittal steel group are withdrawing their employees, and several international airlines are no longer flying to the affected regions.
The local traders and farmers are also reacting: only a few merchants are still leaving their home towns to get supplies.
In some areas in Sierra Leone and Liberia, which are under quarantine, cocoa and coffee beans, which are important for export, are rotting in the fields.
The farmers do not dare to leave their homes for the harvest.
