TWO teenage bushwalkers have been winched to safety after being trapped overnight in the Blue Mountains of NSW.
THE 16-year-old girl and 19-year-old man left Govetts Leap in Blackheath for their tour just after Sunday lunchtime.
Concerned relatives called the police at around 8 p.m. when the two had not returned home.
A search party made up of local police and emergency services left and the couple were found around 11pm near Bridal Veil Falls.
